<div id="review_539354429" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/539354429" />
    <a title="Em*bedded-in-books*" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2481560-em-bedded-in-books"><img alt="Em*bedded-in-books*" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627523857p2/2481560.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/539354429?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Em*bedded-in-books*" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Em*bedded-in-books*" href="/user/show/2481560-em-bedded-in-books">Em*bedded-in-books*</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">young adults who like Indian mysteries</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Em*bedded-in-books* by: </span>
      author
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2481560-em-bedded-in-books?shelf=cozy-mystery">cozy-mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2481560-em-bedded-in-books?shelf=paperback-hardback">paperback-hardback</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2481560-em-bedded-in-books?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer539354429" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2988145903591273597">This was one of the better written books (grammatically as well as content wise) among those churned out in the past few years by newbie Indian authors. Maybe I am a bit biased because I have a natural ken towards mystery genre. This story focuses on the Nayak brothers - pre university college students in their late teens who have a flair for detective work, perhaps influenced by their high ranking Police officer father. It all starts when their close friend is assaulted for seemingly proposing </span>
  <span id="freeText2988145903591273597" style="display:none">This was one of the better written books (grammatically as well as content wise) among those churned out in the past few years by newbie Indian authors. Maybe I am a bit biased because I have a natural ken towards mystery genre. This story focuses on the Nayak brothers - pre university college students in their late teens who have a flair for detective work, perhaps influenced by their high ranking Police officer father. It all starts when their close friend is assaulted for seemingly proposing to a college mate on valentine's day. First they are obtuse as regards to the reason behind the assault, probably jealousy? Later they are dragged into more sinister events. I was drawn into the world of older teens, and longed to have a firsthand knowledge of what it is like to be an older teenage boy. The city of Pune and its suburbs were described in detail, and I got a glimpse into the lifestyle of upper middle class North Indian family. On the whole, a readable book, though it is more suitable to young adults. My rating is actually 3.5 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2988145903591273597" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


